                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2000-06-01</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>Rabinger has a superbly no-nonsense approach to his subject matter, and the book covers every aspect of the life of the documentary film. <P>Parts include: Historical Background, Preproduction, Production, Post-Production, Technical Basics, Projects for Developing Skills, and Career Track. For every area covered he hits the relevant steps and highlights the important issues.<P>The appendices and the annotated bibliography are superb, and the book is worth the price just for these additions.</span>
                  
              
